# CODEOWNERS — ownership by area, mapped to the change-tiering model (`.claude/CONVENTIONS.md` §2).
#
# WHY: review must land on the people who own the risk. Sensitive areas — coaching, safety,
# memory, privacy, notifications, identity, and the model — require the safety/ethics owners
# on every change, because a mistake there costs a user's trust, not minutes (`docs/15 Constitution.md`).
#
# The team handles below are PLACEHOLDERS — replace with real GitHub teams before enabling
# branch protection:
#   @impulse/platform  — backend modular monolith, infra, CI, event bus, data plumbing
#   @impulse/coaching  — Coach/Decision/Identity/Learning engines, prompts, coaching surface
#   @impulse/safety    — Safety Engine, ethics, privacy, the Covenant (the safety/ethics owners)
#   @impulse/ios       — Swift/SwiftUI client, offline-first, navigation
#
# Last matching pattern wins (GitHub semantics), so Sensitive-area rules are placed LAST to
# override broader defaults and force the safety/ethics owners onto those paths.

# ----- Default: everything has an owner -----
*                               @impulse/platform

# ----- Governance & operating-system assets -----
/.github/                       @impulse/platform @impulse/safety
/.claude/                       @impulse/platform
/.claude/CONVENTIONS.md         @impulse/platform @impulse/safety
/.claude/skills/                @impulse/platform
/.claude/skills/behavioral-review/  @impulse/safety @impulse/coaching
/.claude/skills/design-council/     @impulse/safety @impulse/coaching
/.claude/skills/security-review/    @impulse/safety
/.rules/                        @impulse/platform
/.rules/privacy.md              @impulse/safety
/.rules/security.md             @impulse/safety

# ----- Documentation -----
# Canon and most docs are platform-owned; safety/ethics co-owns the sensitive ones.
/docs/                          @impulse/platform

# ----- Architecture & decision records -----
/architecture/                  @impulse/platform
/adr/                           @impulse/platform
/decisions/                     @impulse/safety @impulse/coaching   # PDRs: user-facing behavior & ethics

# ----- iOS client -----
/ios/                           @impulse/ios
*.swift                         @impulse/ios

# ----- Backend engines (modular monolith, `docs/12 Backend Architecture.md`) -----
# Anticipated module layout; adjust paths to the real tree as it lands. Non-sensitive engines
# default to platform; Sensitive engines are overridden below.
/backend/                       @impulse/platform
/backend/engines/decision/      @impulse/coaching
/backend/engines/emotion/       @impulse/coaching
/backend/engines/prompt_builder/  @impulse/coaching

# =========================================================================================
# SENSITIVE AREAS — placed last so they win. These REQUIRE the safety/ethics owners.
